    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Dipturus intermedius (BMNH 1860.8.30.7). Juvenile male (442 mm DL) from Madeira presented to The Natural History Museum, London, by the Rev. Richard Thomas Lowe in 1860." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1285032/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1285034>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Dipturus intermedius (BMNH 1860.8.30.7). Detail of tail showing lateral thorns directed forward, a distinguishing character of the species." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1285034/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1285036>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Raja clavata (BMNH 1860.8.30.5). Juvenile female (144 mm DL) from Madeira presented to The Natural History Museum, London, by the Rev. Richard Thomas Lowe in 1860." ;
